result.name: Menya Ikkyo

reviews.text: Nice food, affordable price, clean environment

This place was one of my favourite Ramen spot, until yesterday. Among other specialties, they have quite a lot of choices for soup, snacks and drinks. They even have kid’s ramen. However quality control has a problem. The same noodle here can vary form wonderful to stunningly salty or spicy. The karaage was crispy and juicy, but there is half a chance that it is sold out. The only real Japanese run restaurant in Shamshuipo, they said, the service didn’t  say the same. Working on Labour ‘s day was frustrating. While I don’t see staff blaming her junior colleague in front of everyone a suitable practice.

What happened was that the senior lady seated 3 pairs of customers at the same time and didn’t point out exactly which stools they should use. Two couples came in and shared one 4 pax table and the third couple sit at the small one. In HK if you are sharing a booth, it is quite common for each couple to sit on one side so you don’t touch someone you don’t know. The first two pairs did so and got grumbling from the lady. She muttered the food order could get wrong because they sit on the wrong side. So the customer asked “do we have to change?” She didn’t reply and left the customers. The young staff took care of them, served water and ordering form. Next, the customer finished their order form for each noodle. They made a mass with the computer. At the end of this event, the girl swallowed all the negative emotions of the lady. We feel sorry for her. I cannot imagine working with that bad tempered and stubborn lady.

The noodle was fine this time but I could not have a good appetite. I may not come back to this shop again.
Not recommended. I can cook instant noodles better than this HK$98 ramen!

The ramen was very good, and with extra noodles was ok as lunch.
The staff is nice, they speak a bit of English, so this helps with the menu.
 The place was clean and you can see the kitchen.
I ordered kimchi ramen and tasted really good.
Very unique style thick cut roast iberico pork use in ramen and thickest soup I have come across , those level of thickness and concentration are normally only found in tsukemen

result.name: 麵屋一京 深水埗本店

reviews.text:
味道唔錯，唔算貴，七八十蚊埋單，好食過附近嘅米芝連車仔麵

仲有唔知係咪轉咗手，個店名叫ボクの拉麺，唔係麵屋一京

佢係正宗日本拉麵，
但都是從日本運過嚟，
中間超溏心金黃，很好吃，面彈牙爽口。🍝🍲
改了名字之后就超难吃 又贵 服务员管理混乱 不会再去噜

由日本師傅主理，由於落單才開始煮，副手才切叉燒，再交畀另一員工加蛋加 配料，共要等10分鐘。

選擇不多但0K，$78一碗算合理。

濃湯較杰，但吃完也不覺太口渴。

建議每張檯都放冰水壺讓客人使用。

麵是可以的
但從沒有等拉麵上菜可以等這麼久
店面也很難有甚麼日本風味可言
店員和師傅做事也很慢
沒有其中一款湯底也沒有在之前說明
